          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">End of an era</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Canadian Prime Minister <a target="_blank" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-01-2025-h3-5-justin-trudeau-has-resigned">Justin Trudeau has resigned</a> as Liberal Party leader after nine years in office. He will remain prime minister until the party selects a new leader through a competitive process. Trudeau faced internal dissent and declining public support due to inflation, housing shortages, and economic challenges. The final straw was the political crisis escalated by Trump's tariffs at the end of 2024.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">His term is marked by progressive policies like legalizing cannabis, affordable child care, dental care, and a national carbon tax, which have faced mounting criticism in recent years. His <a target="_blank" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-01-2025-h3-6-foreign-policy-decisions">foreign policy decisions</a> include Syrian refugee resettlement, pledging a reduction in greenhouse emissions by 30% by 2030, supporting Ukraine in its war against Russia, and voicing for a ceasefire in Palestine. High-profile contenders Mark Carney and Anita Anand are expected to vie for his party's leadership. However, elections later this year <a target="_blank" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-01-2025-h3-7-favor-the-conservatives">favor the Conservatives</a>, led by Pierre Poilievre. Trudeau's resignation ended an era in which the Liberal Party faced significant challenges rebuilding and regaining public trust.
</p>
        </mj-text>
