          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇫🇷 France:</strong> Nicolas Sarkozy <a target="_blank" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-01-2025-br2-10-faces-trial">faces trial</a> over allegations he accepted $51.9 million from Libyan dictator Muammar Gaddafi to fund his 2007 presidential campaign. This follows his recent corruption conviction and house arrest. Arms broker Ziad Takieddine claimed he delivered cash-filled “suitcases” from Libya to Sarkozy but later fled to Lebanon and retracted his testimony, raising concerns about witness tampering. Sarkozy denies the charges, calling them a conspiracy. If convicted, Sarkozy could face prison, marking another blow to his embattled post-presidency legacy.</p>
