          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Why did Ukraine move Christmas to the 25th?</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-7-3.jpg" alt="Why did Ukraine move Christmas to the 25th?" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">In 2023, Ukraine moved its <a target="_blank" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-01-2025-f1-11-official-christmas-celebration">official Christmas celebration</a> to December 25 to align with Western Christian traditions and distinguish itself culturally and religiously from Russia. Historically, Ukraine observed Christmas on January 7, following the Julian calendar used by the Russian Orthodox Church and other Eastern Orthodox churches. The legislation’s sponsors said this change would help Ukranians live their own lives with their traditions and holidays.
</p>
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">This move came as a retaliation to the head of the Russian Orthodox Church, who supported the invasion. Many believed that it was a Western ploy to bring Ukraine closer to Catholic culture. Some say it punishes the Orthodox faith, which should be separated from politics. However, Ukraine is not the first Orthodox country to change Christmas to December 25. Romania, Bulgaria, and Greek Orthodox religious groups also shifted in the past decades. They have done so more out of convenience reasons than political ones. 
</p>
        </mj-text>
